399db8a6252f53c7bba9e25c3ddaaa06b","homepage":"https://github.com/dayongkr/prettier-plugin-sort-re-exports#readme","_nodeVersion":"20.17.0","_npmVersion":"10.8.2","dist":{"integrity":"sha512-tdQVR1WUbJktFp3ExTiXlaWAydZwOOj8ic6AjPV/IZitzjIL34O0v2xNB0X/BnTOx88XUulWeDRgdw2FmU83oA==","shasum":"895c47724c0d38609babef013c851c324536a9c5","tarball":"https://registry.npmjs.org/prettier-plugin-sort-re-exports/-/prettier-plugin-sort-re-exports-0.1.0.tgz","fileCount":6,"unpackedSize":5296,"signatures":[{"keyid":"SHA256:jl3bwswu80PjjokCgh0o2w5c2U4LhQAE57gj9cz1kzA","sig":"MEQCIBPXJYqZXvoAjJmcWKjbHmRTIi3cKcaf9wXcRRGYHrS/AiBeUgCi41SYuwoW0cai8DC19+GLwvM7nparZXF4TJTlxw=="}]},"_npmUser":{"name":"dayongkr","email":"dayongkr@gmail.com"},"directories":{},"maintainers":[{"name":"dayongkr","email":"dayongkr@gmail.com"}],"_npmOperationalInternal":{"host":"s3://npm-registry-packages","tmp":"tmp/prettier-plugin-sort-re-exports_0.1.0_1728204990756_0.7430176162514177"},"_hasShrinkwrap":false}},"time":{"created":"2024-10-06T03:37:33.099Z","modified":"2024-10-06T08:56:31.109Z","0.0.0":"2024-10-06T03:37:33.293Z","0.0.1":"2024-10-06T06:23:27.737Z","0.1.0":"2024-10-06T08:56:30.927Z"},"bugs":{"url":"https://github.com/dayongkr/prettier-plugin-sort-re-exports/issues","email":"dayongkr@gmail.com"},"author":{"name":"dayongkr"},"license":"MIT","homepage":"https://github.com/dayongkr/prettier-plugin-sort-re-exports#readme","keywords":["prettier","plugin","sort","re-exports"],"repository":{"type":"git","url":"git+https://github.com/dayongkr/prettier-plugin-sort-re-exports.git"},"description":"A prettier plugin that sorts the re-exports statements.","maintainers":[{"name":"dayongkr","email":"dayongkr@gmail.com"}],"readme":"# prettier-plugin-sort-re-exports\n\nA [Prettier](https://prettier.io/) plugin to sort re-exports.\n\nThis plugin is not just for sorting exports, but is specifically designed for situations where re-exports are used, such as in barrel files.\n\nTherefore, it performs sorting based on the source, and in cases where separate grouping is required, it sorts only the connected code. For more details, refer to the [example](#example) below.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\nnpm install --save-dev prettier-plugin-sort-re-exports\n```\n\n## Configuration\n\nAdd the plugin to your `.prettierrc` or prettier configuration file:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"plugins\": [\"prettier-plugin-sort-re-exports\"]\n}\n```\n\n## Example\n\n### Sorting re-exports\n\n```javascript\n// Before\nexport { a } from \"./a/foo\";\nexport { b } from \"./a/bar\";\nexport { c } from \"./a/baz\";\n\n// After\nexport { b } from \"./a/bar\";\nexport { c } from \"./a/baz\";\nexport { a } from \"./a/foo\";\n```\n\n### Sorting re-exports with separate groups\n\n```javascript\n// Before\nexport { a } from \"./a/foo\";\nexport { b } from \"./a/bar\";\nexport { c } from \"./a/baz\";\n\nexport { d } from \"./b/foo\";\nexport { e } from \"./b/bar\";\nexport { f } from \"./b/baz\";\n\n// After\nexport { b } from \"./a/bar\";\nexport { c } from \"./a/baz\";\nexport { a } from \"./a/foo\";\n\nexport { e } from \"./b/bar\";\nexport { f } from \"./b/baz\";\nexport { d } from \"./b/foo\";\n```\n\n### Sorting re-exports with separate groups and comments\n\n```javascript\n// Before\n/**\n * Group A\n */\nexport { a } from \"./a/foo\";\nexport { b } from \"./a/bar\";\nexport { c } from \"./a/baz\";\n\n/**\n * Group B\n */\nexport { d } from \"./b/foo\";\nexport { e } from \"./b/bar\";\nexport { f } from \"./b/baz\";\n\n// After\n/**\n * Group A\n */\nexport { b } from \"./a/bar\";\nexport { c } from \"./a/baz\";\nexport { a } from \"./a/foo\";\n\n/**\n * Group B\n */\nexport { e } from \"./b/bar\";\nexport { f } from \"./b/baz\";\nexport { d } from \"./b/foo\";\n```\n","readmeFilename":"README.md"}